**Risks:**
- Low. Option A uses the existing schema; the only assumption being relaxed (Stages count) is already supported by Validate (>=1). Read-side code uses Stages[0]/Refs so it is unaffected by a 2nd stage.
- Watch: ensure the retro-meta stage Output passes validateArtifactRef (valid role identifier 'retro-meta' is [A-Za-z0-9_.-] OK; media_type non-control OK) and that the unreferenced-file guard sees both artifacts (it iterates all stages — confirmed).
- exec_generator meta protocol: keep optional/no-op by default to avoid changing existing generator behavior.

**Gate tier:** Tier 1. Touches the retro write path + manifest CONTENT (a new stage + a new role:retro-meta artifact) + the artifact-attachment model. Even option A (chosen) mutates the write path and introduces a new role; per the bead and dogfood convention that is Tier 1.

